messages.title: Real Change for Scarborough and Whitby
messages.content: So there's an economic recovery? Most people aren't feeling the benefits...

messages.title: A Labour Government will
messages.content: Guarantee a GP appointment in 48 hours...

keyPolicies.policyDescription: Most people aren't feeling the benefits of the economic recovery...
Guarantee a GP appointment in 48 hours, provide more doctors and nurses for our NHS
Raise the minimum wage to £8 an hour, ban exploitative zero hour contracts
Provide 25 hours free childcare for working parents
Cut the deficit more fairly, by making those earning over £150,000 pay more tax
Control immigration so that entitlements to public benefits are earned and wages are not undercut
Build at least 200,000 houses a year by 2020 and ensure a fairer deal for those who rent their homes.
